From myrddincox at gmail.com  Fri May  2 16:33:10 2008
From: myrddincox at gmail.com (Stephen B. Cox)
Date: Fri, 2 May 2008 09:33:10 -0500
Subject: [R-sig-eco] segmented quantile regression and rqss
In-Reply-To: <OF9A295FCC.170AA056-ON8525743D.00498CAC-8525743D.004AF925@epamail.epa.gov>
References: <OF9A295FCC.170AA056-ON8525743D.00498CAC-8525743D.004AF925@epamail.epa.gov>
Message-ID: <fd2477720805020733m437a946bkdbdd23d698599fa4@mail.gmail.com>

Not sure if this is what you are looking for, but just try something like:

m = nlrq(y~g0+g1*x*(x<=bp) + (g1 * bp + b1 * (x-bp))*(x>bp),
data=data, tau=.9,start=list(g0=1,g1=10,b1=-1,bp=5))

where 'bp' is the breakpoint between the two segments.  Obviously -
your starting values would change to fit your needs.

HTH

Stephen

